<topic id='business_definition_learning_difficulty.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Learning Difficulty - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulty</xref>
 is a type of 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_special_education_needs">Special Education Needs</xref>, which affects areas of learning, such as reading, writing, spelling, mathematics etc.        </p>
      <p>
There are several levels of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulties</xref>, such as:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Specific 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulty</xref>
 - a particular difficulty in learning to read, write, spell etc                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Moderate 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulty</xref>
 - achievements well below expected levels in all or most areas of the curriculum, despite appropriate interventions                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Severe 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulty</xref>
 - significant intellectual or cognitive impairments                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Profound and Multiple 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulty</xref>
 - multiple 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulties</xref>
 have severe and complex learning needs, in addition they have other significant difficulties, such as physical disabilities or a sensory impairment.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_learning_difficulty">Learning Difficulties</xref>, see the mentalhealth.org.uk website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.mentalhealth.org.uk/learning-disabilities/a-to-z/l/learning-difficulties"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Learning difficulties</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <i>
Note: a 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_learning_disability">Learning Disability</xref>
 usually has a significant impact on a 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>'s life. A 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
 with a 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_learning_disability">Learning Disability</xref>
 finds it harder than others to learn, understand and communicate.            </i>
      </p>
  </div>
